		<br>
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		 <tr>
		   <td><font face="verdana" size="2"> I found it rather interesting that you didn't even bother to comment on
the lack of clothing on EverQuest characters. You did mention that it was in fact a female who pushed for characters to have tight, hard bodies and healthy endowments, but failed to notice and or comment that it is possible for beautiful people to wear clothing and still be beautiful. I am just a
little tired of all the male teenagers, who obviously have never gotten within
ten feet of a real woman, constantly making comments about my barbarian's *healthy endowment*.<P>

 A female barbarian wishing for a really large cloak to hide in.

<P> <P><b><i>
<font face="Georgia" size="4" color="#9F3215">
Milo Says:
</font></i></b><BR>

   ... and *I'm* tired of all the e-mails that I get of the flavor
"EverQuest is
sexist."  They aren't warranted at all.  If you want to play the type of
character who's demure, then why are you playing a barbarian?  Barbarians
typically don't care too much about the way they dress; they have higher
priorities (killing, arguing, eating, copulating, etc.), so pretty much
whatever
gets the job done is enough.<P>

   You people who like to moan about EQ's scantily-clad female characters
have chosen to ignore the fact that the high elves, gnomes, dwarves,
humans, erudites, and Iksar women are fully clothed virtually from head to
toe -- and head to ankle, in the case of the halflings.  Then, of course,
there
are the trolls and the ogres, of whose more revealing clothing no one
complains.<P>

   The dark elves, woodland elves, half-elves, and barbarians aren't the
only races in the game.  You people need to stop pretending that they are,
just so you can complain about them being half naked.  I'm going to ignore
this brand of whining, from now on.<P>

<HR align="center" width="85%"><P>

 i Learned, to spoke in grade First.,<P>
 
 Just bugging you. 8)<P>

 Anyway I read some of the articles here and saw that you insult people who do not take the time to learn english. BAD MISTAKE. Although I am certain that you do not seem to know the protocol of "International Product Marketing". I think the first rule is not to insult the consumer, but to keep them happy. Now as you know, Ever Quest is a game that is played all across the world. Also it is mostly played by KIDS! That's right, the people who are still attending school and learning these concepts. I live in Toronto (The most multi-cultural city on the planet) and have seen good people like you burned for saying things that you do not mean.<P> 

 Did you know that "English is not a difficult language to master" is considered a racial remark? The reason for this, is that it is imposing that the english language is superior, and is far easier to learn then any other language! Now I know that this is not what you meant or what other people might have thought you meant. However this was my impression when you made this remark.<P>

 Please be more conscious about how you reply to some of these e-mail. I suggest that you write up an apology to the person who asked you an honest question.

 Webbie<P>
 
 PS. since you like to nitpick, I apologize for any mistakes I might have made while writing you this letter. I am still in school myself and was dyslexic for a time when my parents got divourced. (because of stress) Also I am sorry for any extra U's I put into the words because of my canadian accent. <P>

 i.e. Honour = Honor<P>
 
 Jim Webster

<P> <P><b><i>
<font face="Georgia" size="4" color="#9F3215">
Milo Says:
</font></i></b><BR>

   On the contrary, EverQuest's English-speaking player base is composed
chiefly of people who should have high school diplomas (if not college
degrees), and thus a firm grasp of the language.<P>

<HR align="center" width="85%"><P>

 Hey there are a few monsters that I think should be added... maybe they are but I haven't seen them hehe... well one is a hydra (you know one of them seven headed dragons)... another cool addition I think you should add is a daemon or demon I always wonder why you never put those too in... but if anyone could do it I was hoping it would be you! Let me know what you think on them two monsters :D  I know you know that these would make an awsome addition and you will get working on 3d models for soon!!!!<P>

 hehe well I found two more that should be added hope you can make awsome models for them here they are medusa, dinjin (genie), and the two other I sent you hydra (seven headed dragon), and a demon or daemon<P>

 Nick
<P> <P><b><i>
<font face="Georgia" size="4" color="#9F3215">
Milo Says:
</font></i></b><BR>
   There are already medusae and djinns in the game.  As for the hydra and
the demon, we considered putting those into the game a long time ago, but
they were no-gos because:<P>

   (1) The hydra would require a massive number of polygons, and would
         pretty much annihilate most (if not all) players' frame rates.<P>

   (2) The demon is associated with several real-world, modern day
religions.
         We didn't want them in the game any more than we wanted Jesus
         Christ or Buddha in it.<P>

<HR align="center" width="85%"><P>

 I am writing only to expose a word that you used improperly.<P>

 "I'm not from Lima, Ohio. I was just born there. I lived there for a very, very brief time, and all that I remember about my life there is that it snowed, that I lived in a trailer or something, and that I got chicken
pox, I think. I was raised in Las Vegas."<P>

 People are reared not raised.<P>

 Taylania<BR>
 EQ addict

<P> <P><b><i>
<font face="Georgia" size="4" color="#9F3215">
Milo Says:
</font></i></b><BR>

   "Raised" is an officially accepted synonym for "reared."  Thank you
for playing.<P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

 In future products, do you plan to do more with the faces of characters, such as blinking, twitching (perhaps on the more primitive races), mouths moving, and the EQ emotes?  Sure, we have /cry, but it'd be great if the character could frowm, close his eyes, and possibly even shed a tear.<P>

 Zuckuss Gand

