<HR align="center" width="85%"><P>

 I just wanted to thank you for all your hard work on the characters--both in the original EverQuest game and in the expansion.<BR>
They are quite splendid.<P>

 I also wanted to state that I agree with your theory on the English language and the people who have horrible grammar (and couldn't care
less). Furthermore, I agree with your view on Jewel getting her teeth fixed.  But then again, most humans basically want to become as perfect as possible.  I try to avoid generalizations, but I still have yet to see
this postulate disproved.<P>

 I do, however, have a question to present to you, though it has nothing to do with EverQuest:<P>

 If there were one thing you could change about your past, what would it
be?<P>

 I like to play mind games, and am quite anxious to hear your answer. Perhaps you can appreciate that; if not, I hope you are not insulted by
it. Many thanks for your time.<P>

 Bain Brendanoor<BR>
 Lord Captain of Thorce Castle, Mylansia

<P> <P><b><i>
<font face="Georgia" size="4" color="#9F3215">
Milo Says:
</font></i></b><BR>

   Besides investing in Microsoft, I wish that I had spent more time playing
musical instruments as a child.  Music is immeasurably important to me,
and it kills me that I have never devoted as much time to it as my passion
for it warrants.  Although I rather enjoy my current job and the financial
security it affords me, I would possess a keener intellect and be generally
more agreeable if I had devoted my life to the organization of sound.<P>

